<CENTER><H3>Sec. 204 (16 USC 1404) Reports</H3></CENTER>

<P>The Commission shall transmit to Congress, by January 31 of
each year, a report which shall include--
<UL>
<P>(1) a description of the activities and accomplishments of the
Commission during the immediately preceding year; and 

<P>(2) all the findings and recommendations made by and to the
Commission pursuant to section 1402 of this title together with
the responses made to these recommendations.
</UL>
