<HEAD><TITLE>MMPA Sec. 403 (16 USC 1421b)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#800080">
<P><A NAME="Top of page"></A><A HREF="mmpacont.html"> Return to MMPA Table of Contents</A>
<P><A HREF="mmpa402.html">Go to previous section</A>
<CENTER><H3>Sec. 403 (16 USC 1421b) Stranding response agreements</H3></CENTER>

<P>(a) [<STRONG>In general</STRONG>] -- The Secretary may enter into an agreement
under section 1382(c) of  this title with any person to take
marine mammals under section  1379(h)(1) of this title in
response to a stranding.

<P>(b) [<STRONG>Required provision</STRONG>] -- An agreement authorized by
subsection (a) of this section shall--
<UL>
<P>(1) specify each person who is authorized to perform
activities under the agreement; and

<P>(2) specify any terms and conditions under which a person so
specified may delegate that authority to another person. 
</UL>
<P>(c) [<STRONG>Review</STRONG>] -- The Secretary shall periodically review
agreements under section  1382(c) of this title that are entered
into pursuant to this subchapter,  for performance adequacy and
effectiveness.

