<TD  WIDTH=10%><BR></TD>

<TD  ROWSPAN=2 WIDTH=75%>
<H2>KMPC JOB OPENINGS</H2>


<HR ALIGN=LEFT  SIZE=3  WIDTH=100%>


</TR>
</TD>
</TABLE>


<TABLE  CELLPADDING=3 CELLSPACING=2  BORDER=0  WIDTH=85%>

<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><STRONG><FONT SIZE=4>IS & Engineering Department Coordinator For KABC/KLOS/KMPC Radio</FONT></STRONG></TD>

<TR><TD>
KABC/KLOS/KMPC, Los Angeles.<BR>
Responsible for the maintenance, administration and user support of local area network and PC's and assisting in the engineering
department by coordinating supply inventories, purchases, vendor schedules etc. at the LA radio facility.  Applicant is to be
Novell certified CNA, have good organizational, verbal and written skills and a valid drivers license.  A working knowledge of 
Netware 3.XX, Microsoft Windows and Windows 95 system administration is required.  Experience with Microsoft Mail, Excel, Word, WordPerfect
and Lotus desirable.

Mail a tape, cover letter and resume to:<BR>
Norm Avery<BR>
Director Radio Engineering, KABC/KLOS/KMPC<BR>
3321 South La Cienega Blvd.<BR>
Los Angeles, CA, 90016<BR>
Please no phone or fax<br>
EOE
<BR><BR>
</TD>



<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><STRONG><FONT SIZE=4>News Anchor</FONT></STRONG></TD>

<TR><TD>
KABC-AM, Los Angeles.<BR>
3+ years major market experience. Requires strong writing skills and conversational delivery. Should demonstrate proficiency in news actuality gathering and editing. Journalism or Communications degree preferred. Mail a tape, cover letter and resume to:<BR>
Andy Ludlum<BR>
Program Manger<BR>
3321 South La Cienega Blvd.<BR>
Los Angeles, CA, 90016<BR>
EOE
<BR><BR>
</TD>

<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER><STRONG><FONT SIZE=4>News Reporter</FONT></STRONG></TD>
<TR><TD>
KABC-AM, Los Angeles.<BR>
3+ years major market experience. Requires strong, live reporting skills, especially breaking news. Excellent writing and interview skills required. Some talk show hosting experience desirable. Journalism or Communications degree preferred. Mail a tape, cover letter and resume to:<BR>
Andy Ludlum<BR>
Program Manager<BR>
3321 South La Cienega Blvd.<BR>
Los Angeles, CA, 90016<BR>
EOE
<BR><BR>

</TD></TR>
