<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>KMPC Talents: "Terrell and Katz Show"</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=ffffff TEXT=#000000 LINK=#FF0000 VLINK=#CC0000 ALINK=#0000FF>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<IMG SRC=TK.gif ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 VSPACE=10 BORDER=2>
<H1>"Terrell and Katz Show"</H1>
<H3>Monday - Friday<BR> Noon - 3 p.m.</H3>
<P>
 

<P>Tune in the "Terrell and Katz Show" weekdays from Noon to 3 p.m. on 710 Talk / KMPC. <A HREF="../Bios/LT.htm">Leo Terrell</A> 
and <A HREF="../Bios/BK.htm">Burt Katz</A> engage in entertaining and thought-provoking discussions regarrding news events 
and the latest legal issues and cases. With years of experience within the judicial system, both 
Terrell and Katz offer valuable insight to the legal system through their point/counterpoint 
show. The show covers all angles from both the conservative and liberal viewpoints.<P>

<P>Burt Katz served as a prosecutor in the Los Angeles County District Attorney's Office for 14 
years, during which he specialized in celebrated homicide cases. He may be best known for his 
work as one of the chief prosecutors in the Charles Manson family murders. He later became a Superior 
Court Judge where he presided for nine years over many controversial and celebrated cases. He 
has also supervised and presided over Juvenile Courts, working closely with delinquent children, 
Juvenile Judges and experts.<P>

<P>Leo Terrell is a former High School teacher who graduated from the U.C.L.A. Law School. He began 
his career in civil rights in the state of Arkansas. After passing the California Bar Exam, 
Terrell returned to Los Angeles, where he established his own law practice. He has served as 
Legal Redress Counsel for the Los Angeles Chapter of the NAACP and has been involved in many 
other organizations with goals such as the control and elimination of hate-crime, and the 
establishment of improved race relations. In addition to participating in public service 
activities, Terrell has provided extensive media coverage of important civil rights proceedings, 
such as the Rodney King and Reginald Denny trials.<P>


<P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR CLEAR=ALL></BR>
<BR  CLEAR="ALL">

