<A NAME=RUBIN><TABLE CELLSPACING=6	CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%><TR><TD><B>SAM RUBIN</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Saturday 1 - 4 p.m.</TD></TR><TR><TD><IMG SRC=SR.jpg HSPACE=10 VSPACE=4 BORDER=2 ALIGN=left>
<P><A HREF="../Bios/SR.htm">Sam Rubin</A> covers entertainment on 710 TALK / KMPC -- from theater and television to movies and celebrity interviews.  Listeners are drawn to this fast-paced program. He also contributes entertainment reports during "The Peter Tilden Show with Tracey Miller Show." Sam is well known in Los Angeles for his work as the "KTLA Morning News" Entertainment Reporter for which he covers a broad spectrum of entertainment industry news. <P><P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<!-------------------------------MERRILL SHINDLER------------------------------------------------>

<A NAME=MERRILL></A>
<TABLE CELLSPACING=6    CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%>
<TR><TD><B>"MERRILL SHINDLER with DERALEE SCANLON"</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Saturday 4 - 7 p.m.</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><IMG VSPACE=4 HSPACE=10 BORDER=0 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="merrillS.jpg">
<A HREF="../Bios/MS.htm">Merrill Shindler</A>, renowned KABC Talkradio food lover and critic, author of LA's Zagat Guide to 
Eating Entertainment, recently lost 18 pounds and cut his cholesterol by 80 points. He was reborn, rejuvenated and inspired. 
So he teamed up with <A HREF="../Bios/DS.htm">Deralee Scanlon</A>, a prominent TV nutritionist/dietitian to develop a new 
show concept: "Lite and Lively: How to Make Sense Out of Eating Sensibly." <P>This is not how to survive on tofu, bean 
sprouts and macrobiotic brown rice diets. This is how to balance out your Wednesday cheeseburger and fries lunch with a 
light, healthy dinner. It's a realistic, sane, very human and humane approach on how to eat to stay healthy. And, since 
Merrill is hosting it with challenging banter from Deralee, it's pretty much a "hoot" for listeners. <P><P></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<!----------------------------------STEVE PARKER-------------------------------------------->

<A NAME=PARKER></A><TABLE CELLSPACING=6	CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%><TR><TD><B>STEVE PARKER "THE CAR NUT"</B></TD></TR><TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Saturday 7 - 10 p.m.</TD></TR><TR><TD><IMG SRC=SPa.jpg HSPACE=10 VSPACE=4 BORDER=2 ALIGN=left><P>There is good reason why <A HREF="../Bios/SP.htm">Steve Parker</A> is called "The Car Nut." He loves cars and loves to talk about them. Every Saturday, Steve reviews the latest trends in the automotive world, from the newest cars off the assembly line to the celebrities who love to drive them.  Steve is alsoknown as the "Car Dude" on KTLA-TV channel 5 and nationally on Tribunetelevision.  Click <A HREF="../SendEmail/home.cgi?thecarnut@cis.compuserve.com">here</A> to email Steve for comments and questions about his show.<P><P><CENTER><A HREF="../Parker/home.htm">Click here to see Steve Parker's Road Test</A></CENTER></TD></TR></TABLE><!---------------------------------THE GARDEN HOTLINE----------------------------------------><A NAME=GARDEN><TABLE CELLSPACING=6	CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%><TR><TD><B>"THE GARDEN HOTLINE"</B></TD></TR><TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Sunday 5 - 8 a.m.</TD></TR><TR><TD><IMG SRC=RS.jpg HSPACE=10 VSPACE=4 BORDER=2 ALIGN=left><P>Ralph Snodsmith is host of "The Garden Hotline" heard on 710 TALK / KMPC. Well known nationally for his appearances on "Good Morning America", Ralph has educated millions about the joys of gardening through his radio show, his syndicated newspaper column "The Garden Hotline", and more than 25 years of teaching at the New York Botanical Garden. Since 1984 he's written the gardening section of the Americana Encyclopedia Yearbook. Ralph wins awards as he cultivates listeners. Most recently (1992) he was presented with the American Horticultural Society Communications Award. He's respected by those who know their roots.<P><P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--------------------------------GINA SMITH-----------------------------------------------><A NAME=GINA><TABLE CELLSPACING=6	CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%><TR><TD><B>"ON COMPUTERS" WITH GINA SMITH</B></TD></TR><TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Sunday 8 - 10 a.m.</TD></TR><TR><TD><IMG SRC=GS.jpg HSPACE=10 VSPACE=4 BORDER=2 ALIGN=left><P>Every Sunday, this fast-moving, upbeat program covers all aspects of personal computing without getting bogged down in techno jabber. It is aimed at the non-"pocket protector" types, and gets into everything from hardware to software and personal computing's rapidly growing social issues. "On Computers" is a call-in show that also features guests from the computer industry, as well as a regular staple of contributors. In addition to being the host of "On Computers," Gina Smith is a contributor to "Good Morning America" (you can see her every Wednesday) and writes regular columns for the Hollywood Reporter, <I>The Los Angeles Times</I>, <I>Wired</I> and<I> Glamour</I>. Gina also writes her own newsletter, <I>Download</I>. <P><P></TD></TR></TABLE><!-----------------------------------LEE MIRABAL-------------------------------------------><A NAME=MIRABAL></A><TABLE CELLSPACING=6 CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%><TR><TD><B>LEE MIRABAL</B></TD></TR><TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Sunday 1  - 4 p.m.</TD></TR><P></TD></TR></TABLE><!-----------------------------------ELMER DILLS-------------------------------------------><A NAME=ELMER></A><TABLE CELLSPACING=6 CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%><TR><TD><B>ELMER DILLS</B></TD></TR><TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Sunday 4 - 7 p.m.</TD></TR><TR><TD><IMG VSPACE=4 HSPACE=10 BORDER=0 ALIGN=LEFT SRC="elmerD.jpg">Since 1977, KABC Talkradio listeners have turned to <A HREF="../Bios/ED.htm">Elmer Dills</A>, Southern California's favorite restaurant critic and travel specialist, for ideas about leisure activities throughout the Southland. A former diplomat who entertained heads of state, Elmer has experienced the best (and worst) of wining and dining throughout the world. <P>With regular reports on Orange County, Hawaii, Santa Barbara, the Inland Empire, Palm Springs and the Desert, Elmer makes it easy to find the greatest bargains in dining and travel. He also shares his expert advice on wine selection (including the best bargains!) and gives his listeners tips on the 
best Bed and Breakfast Inns and where to go for Sunday Brunch.<P>When Elmer talks about restaurants or places to stay - 
people go. <P><P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<!----------------------------------Paxton Quigley----------------------------------------------->

<A NAME=PAXTON><TABLE CELLSPACING=6 CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=0 WIDTH=85%>
<TR><TD><B>"EMPOWERMENT HOUR WITH PAXTON QUIGLEY "</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD>710 TALK / KMPC<BR>Sunday 7 - 8 p.m.<P></TD></TR>

<TR><TD><IMG SRC=PQ.jpg HSPACE=10 VSPACE=4 BORDER=2 ALIGN=left>
America's first lady of personal reliance and gun-safety host a lively, interactive hour on "staying healthy," inside and out.
Her expert, outspoken, cutting edge 710 TALK/KMPC conversations inspire knowledge and growth.  Traversing the galaxy from 
guns to glamour to gastritis, with smart-talk stops at crime, politics, health, personal defense, alternative medicine, and 
occasinal chats with extraterrestrials, the Empowerment Hour scores a bulls-eye with women of all ages and the men in
their lives who truly care about them.<P><P>
</TD>
