<HEAD>
<TITLE>Xavier Hermosillo

</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>XAVIER HERMOSILLO
</H1>

      <FONT SIZE=5>Monday to Friday<br> 7 - 9 p.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>During his media career, Xavier has worked as a radio news reporter, 
television commentator, newspaper sports writer, editor and photographer.<P>
<P>
  

He maintains a hectic schedule off the air, as well.  Xavier is the 
State Chairman of the Republican National Hispanic Assembly of 
California, and the official Latino auxiliary of the California Republican 
Party.  He served as Deputy Chairman for the California 
Latino Bus Campaign (1992).<P>
<P>


In addition to hosting his show on 710 TALK / KMPC, Xavier is seen on 
KCOP - TV's Channel 13 "Real News".  His news commentary each Thursday 
evening serves as the counter-balance to Bill Press, who is Chairman of 
the California Democratic Party.<P>
<P>


	Hermosillo is also President of his own public relations and government 
affairs firm, which specializes in the areas of crisis public relations, 
marketing and government affairs.<P> <P>
  
	A lifelong resident of Los Angeles and the community of San Pedro,  
Xavier is married and has five children.<P> <P

</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
