<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Maureen Lesourd
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     	<TD><IMG SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     	<TD WIDTH=75% >
	<H1>MAUREEN LESOURD</H1>

	<FONT SIZE=5>KMPC President and General Manager<BR></FONT></TD></TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>


<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>
	<P>Maureen Lesourd, a veteran radio, television and advertising executive, was named President and General Manager of KABC-AM / KMPC-AM / KSFO-FM on May  1, 1996. She is responsible for the operations of the three Los Angeles properties which are among the 21 radio stations throughout the U.S. owned and operated by Capital Cities/ABC Inc., a subsidiary of the Walt Disney Company.
<P>
	<P>Most of Lesourd's broadcast experience has been in radio. In 1981, she began her career with Capital Cities/ABC, Inc. in sales, as an Account Executive with WPLJ-FM in New York City. Shortly afterward, she was promoted to Sales Manager for the station in 1983, a position she held until 1988, when she was promoted to President and General Manager of WRQX-FM in Washington, D.C.
<P>
	<P>She left Capital Cities/ABC, Inc. in 1993 to become Vice President and General Manager of WQCD-FM, Tribune Broadcasting's NAC/Jazz station in New York City. During her two years, the station achieved exceptional ratings growth and earned a National Association of Broadcasters Marconi Award for Excellence in the format in 1993.
<P>
	<P>Lesourd rejoined Capital Cities/ABC, Inc. in January, 1995, as Senior Vice President of Affiliate Relations for the ABC Television Network, reporting to David Westin, President of the ABC Television Network Group. In this position, she oversaw all ABC Television Affiliate Relations activities and departments, including Station Relations, Station Operations, Affiliate Research and Affiliate Marketing Services.
<P>
	<P>In addition to her broadcast experience, Lesourd's career includes account management at Grey Advertising, where she was an Account Executive on both packaged goods and retail accounts from 1978 to 1981. Prior to joining the advertising agency, Maureen was Operations Director at Storer Broadcasting's station, WHN-AM, in New York from 1976 to 1978, and Traffic Manager at Press Broadcasting's stations, WJLK-AM/FM in New Jersey from 1969 to 1976.
<P>
	<P>Lesourd was formerly on the Board of Directors of the Advertising Council. In 1990, she served as Chairman of the Washington Area Broadcasters, and in 1991, as Chairman of the Radio Committee for the United Way.
<P>
	<P>Maureen Lesourd was born and raised in the New York / New Jersey area and is a graduate of Monmouth College in West Long Branch, New Jersey. She currently resides with her husband, David, in Los Angeles, California.

<P>



</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>


