<HEAD>
<TITLE>CHUCK MADDEN
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>CHUCK MADDEN
</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>Morning Show Sports Reporter</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>
<P>        Chuck Madden is the sports reporter for the "Peter Tilden Show
with Tracey Miller," heard weekdays from 5:30 to 9 a.m. on 710 TALK / KMPC.
His odd sense of humor and entertaining approach to sports are a perfect
complement to the hilarious morning talk show.<P> 

<P>         Madden was raised in Rochester, New York, and moved to Dallas at
age 10.  He remained there through high school, then, continued his
education at a small college in Alabama, where he earned a degree in
Chemistry. After college, Madden returned to Dallas where he enrolled in a
six-week broadcasting course. There, armed with his broadcasting
certificate, he was hired at a radio station in a small Louisiana town.
That job propelled him to a succession of other radio spots in such markets
as Joplin, Missouri; Dallas, Texas; Huron, South Dakota; and Monterey and
San Jose in California.<P> 

<P>          In 1993, Chuck joined KMPC as a sports talk show host. When
Capital Cities / ABC purchased the station, he became the morning sports
reporter. Madden also hosted a Sunday sports show that was broadcast live
from Trophys in Newport Beach.<P> 

<P>         Madden enjoys watching sports on the weekends as well as catching
up on movies. He is single and lives in Long Beach, California.<P> 
<P> 



</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
