<HEAD>
<TITLE>Tracey Miller

</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>TRACEY MILLER
</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>"The Tracey Miller Show" <BR>
  Monday - Friday 5 - 9 a.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>Tracey Miller has been a successful radio broadcaster for the past 
15 years.  Her sharp sense of humor, stand-out radio voice and journalistic skills have made her one of the premier talk show hosts in Los Angeles.<P>
<P>


Tracey has proven that women have a voice in drive-time radio.  Prior to 
joining Peter Tilden on KMPC-AM, Tracey co-hosted a morning talk show on 
KFI-AM. In addition, she hosted her own successful entertainment talk 
show, Tracey Miller's Celebrity File, which combined in-studio 
guests, funny gossip, and movie and television reviews.<P> <P>

She joined Peter Tilden's KABC Talkradio afternoon program in January of 
1994, and in May, 1995, "The Peter Tilden Show with Tracey Miller" moved 
to mornings on 710 TALK / KMPC.<P> <P>


Tracey is an award-winning broadcast journalist.  She has been 
honored with first-place awards for her radio work as reporter, writer 
and editor by the Radio and Television News Association (four Golden 
Mike Awards), Associated Press, United Press International, Sigma Delta 
Chi and the National Association of Press Women.<P> <P>

 
In addition to being a radio broadcaster, Tracey has written humorous 
articles for <I>The Los Angeles Times</I> Lifestyle section.  She is a 
single mother of two girls and lives in Glendale.<P> <P>

</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
