<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>STEVE PARKER
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>STEVE PARKER

</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>"THE CAR NUT"<BR>Saturday 7 to 10 p.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>
Steve Parker's live radio call-in show "The Car Nut" is heard on 710 TALK / KMPC in Los Angeles 
every Saturday afternoon from 2 to 4 p.m.  Focusing on new products, worldwide car industry news 
and personalities in the auto industry, "The Car Nut" is a different kind of automotive radio 
show - it's entertaining.<P>

"The KTLA Car Dudes," featuring Steve Parker, is seen every Friday morning on the "KTLA Morning 
News," the Emmy-winning number one rated local morning show in America.  Steve Parker has served 
as host and associate segment-producer since the first week the show went on the air, in July, 
1991.  The Car Dudes segment is also seen every Friday night on the "KTLA News At Ten," the 
number one rated broadcast to the seven Tribune Entertainment-owned television stations in 
America including those in New York City, Piladelphia, Chicago, New Orleans, Miami and Denver.<P>

Parker has also guested with Tom Snyder on his television program and several times on "The 
Larry King Show" and as an expert guest with radio and television stations nationwide.  He is 
also quoted regularly as an analyst in consumer and auto/motorcycle industry publications. Steve 
wrote, segment-produced and starred in America on the Road, a half-hour ESPN special broadcast 
nationally in November, 1993.<P>

Steve has also served as an editor of Popular Mechanics, Four Wheel and Off-Road, Automotive 
Fleet, Sports Car Illustrated and other magazines and has contributed to more than 150 other 
publications worldwide.  He has traveled extensively worldwide covering the "automotive beat."

</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
