<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sam Rubin
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>SAM RUBIN
</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>Saturdays<BR> 1 to 4 p.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>

<P>Over the past 15 years, Sam Rubin has established himself as a
key television entertainment reporter and radio personality.  Since 1991,
Sam's humorous style has contributed strongly to the popularity of KTLA -
TV's weekday Morning News. On Saturdays, he hosts an entertainment show on
710 TALK / KMPC, from 12 to 2 p.m.<P> 

<P>         Rubin was born in Los Angeles and attended nearby Occidental
College, where he attained his Bachelor of Arts in American Studies and
Rhetoric.  Rubin's other areas of concentrated studies included English,
History, Economics and Public Speaking.<P> 

<P>         In addition to his Los Angeles jobs, Rubin currently reports for
KTVU-TV in San Francisco, and "Show Buzz," a nationally syndicated
television show out of Canada. He also produces The Entertainment Report,
which is syndicated in the United States and internationally, and has also
produced and reported for Personalities and Fox Entertainment News, both
produced for the Fox Television Network.<P> 

<P>         Rubin has also found time to co-author two biographies, one about
Jacqueline Onassis, the other on Mia Farrow.  His other publishing credits
include articles in McCalls, Home and The Los Angeles Times.  Rubin can
also frequently be seen as a regular contributor of Hollywood news on
various television broadcasts.<P> 

<P>         In his free time, Rubin enjoys relaxing with his wife Julie and
their newborn daughter, Perry (born June 13, 1995).  The family takes
pleasure in getting involved in running events and going to the movies and
theater.<P> 
<P> 


</TD>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>


