<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Deralee Scanlon
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>DERALEE SCANLON

</H1>

<FONT SIZE=5>"Dining Out with Merrill Shindler"<BR>
                                   Saturday 4 - 7 p.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>Deralee Scanlon co-hosts the "Light 'n Lively Hour" from 4 to 5 p.m. as part of Merrill Shindler's popular restaurant radio show on KABC Talkradio, broadcast on Saturdays from 4 to 7 p.m. Deralee is a Registered Dietitian with expertise in a variety of dietetic areas, including: nutritional assessment, diet therapy for disease prevention, nutrition for senior citizens, weight management and lifestyle counseling. <P>She has also been heard on such radio programs as "The Tom Snyder Show," KABC's "Michael Jackson Show," and on many radio interviews throughout the U.S.

<P>In January 1993, Ms. Scanlon was honored by the California Dietetic Association with the award as California Dietitian of the Year in Private Practice, Business or Communication.

<P>Ms. Scanlon is the author of Diets That Work, published May 1991 in hard-cover by the Lowell House division of RGA Publishing Group, with updated editions for 1992 and 1993. Her earlier work, The Wellness Book of I.B.S., was published December 1989 in hard-cover by St. Martin's Press in New York and as a trade paperback December 1991. Currently, she is working on her third book.

<P>Ms. Scanlon has made more than 400 appearances in the media as a nutrition authority. She has been seen regularly on local and national television, including Cable News Network (CNN), the "Vicki Show," "Suzanne Sommers Show," KCAL-TV's "Live in L.A.," KTLA-TV's "Morning New Show," NBC-TV's "Marilu Henner Show," and more than 25 segments as a regular on ABC-TV network's "The Home Show," as well as weekly segments on KTTV-TV's "Good Day L.A." Deralee served as a nutrition reporter in a series of nutritionally-oriented segments for the MED/NIWS service syndicate to ABC-Television stations throughout the nation. 

<P>Ms. Scanlon's column appears regularly in The Natural Way magazine. Articles by or about Ms. Scanlon or her work have also appeared in such magazines as Model, New Woman, Longevity, Health World, and L.A. Parent (where she is a contributing writer), and in such newspapers as The Los Angeles Times.

<P>Ms. Scanlon provides corporate nutrition consultation involving the formulation and development of new food products, and participates in their strategic marketing planning based on consumer-driven trends. 

<P>She has hosted a supermarket tour segment in a video film produced by Dr. Art Ulene for the American Medical Association's "Campaign Against Cholesterol," for use in hospitals nationally. In addition, she has served as spokesperson for a number of health-oriented products, as well as for the California Milk Advisory Board's introduction of a new, calcium-enriched line. Earlier, she was appointed spokesperson and nutrition consultant for the Irvine Ranch Farmers Markets, a chain of upscale markets.

<P>While with Irvine Ranch, Ms. Scanlon created a weekly "Ask the Dietitian" newspaper column. Its success in drawing reader response resulted in her re-introduction of the column, on a continuing basis, for a group of Southern California newspapers. 

<P>Upon graduation with a B.S. in Food and Science at Cal State-L.A., second highest in her class after four years on the Dean's Honor List, Ms. Scanlon provided counseling for both corporate and individual clients. During that time, she was approached by a public company seeking to expand its weight management plan on a nationwide basis as part of the growing trend toward industry workforce wellness programs. She joined that firm as Vice-President, Corporate Sales and Nutrition Counsel, and created and supervised a field network of thirty Registered Dietitians throughout the U.S.

<P>Having worked with thousands of "diet patients" and having analyzed the problems that too often result in failure and frustration, Ms. Scanlon left her position and returned to private practice and the media, in order to better inform consumers about safe, healthful lifestyle eating management and successful dieting techniques.

<P> As a member of the National Speakers Association, Ms. Scanlon lectures to organizations and other groups on the subjects of nutrition for health and beauty, effective lifestyle management, and the special nutritional needs of the "baby boomer" generation. She has taught courses on Weight Management and Nutrition for Seniors at Emeritus College, and has lectured at the UCLA Medical Center.

<P>Prior to attending Cal State-L.A., Ms. Scanlon studied Medical Record Science at East Los Angeles College, where she earned the Medical Record Association award for scholastic achievement. Subsequently, she became an accredited Medical Record Technician, and received her Associate of Arts Degree from Santa Monica City College before entering Cal State-L.A. For several years, extending into early college, Ms. Scanlon worked throughout the world as a fashion and photography model, including extensive appearances in Paris' Pret a Porte fashion collections, and in such leading magazines as Vogue.

<P>In 1991 and 1992, Deralee Scanlon served the membership of Dietitians in Business and Communications (DBC) as Geographic Representative for Area 1, which covers eight Western states. She also served as Southern California Chairperson for DBC and is the current national DBC newsletter editor. Deralee is a member of the following additional organizations: the American Dietetic Association, California Dietetic Association, Society for Nutrition Education, National Speakers Association, and American Federation of Television and Radio Artists (AFTRA). Ms Scanlon is profiled in both the 1994/1995 and 1995/1996 editions of "Who's Who in the West."



</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<P>

