<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>MERRILL SHINDLER
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     	<TD><IMG SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     	<TD WIDTH=75% >
	<H1>MERRILL SHINDLER</H1>

	<FONT SIZE=5>"Dining Out with Merrill Shindler"<BR>
	Saturday  4 - 7 p.m.</FONT></TD>	
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>
<TD>

A well known restaurant critic, Merrill Shindler can be heard on KABC Talkradio on Saturday 
4 to 7 p.m. Shindler's "Dining Out" show is aimed at discovering new and unique restaurants in 
Southern California from ethnic hole-in-the-walls to the trendiest watering holes, sharing his 
discoveries with his hungry restaurant savy audience.<P>

<P>A restaurant critic for a decade 
for the former Los Angeles Herald Examiner, Shindler now writes about restaurants for the 
<I>Zagat Restaurant Survey, LA Reader, and The Daily Breeze</I>.  In 
addition, Merrill writes a weekly restaurant column for the Thomson Newspapers that includes 
<I>The Pasadena Star News, San Gabriel Valley Tribune</I> and <I>The Whittier Daily News</I>.<P>


<P>A Graduate of New York University with a M.A. in film criticism and aesthetics, Shindler 
has traveled extensively throughout Europe, Mexico, and Central America, landing in San 
Francisco where he began working for the <I>San Francisco Bay Guardian</I>. While at the 
Guardian, Shindler was the entertainment editor and restaurant critic. He also wrote columns on 
entertainment for <I>San Francisco Magazine</I> and became the west coast editor for <I>Rolling 
Stone Magazine</I>.<P>

<P>	Shindler has been head writer for Casey Kasem's American Top 
Forty radio show and  Kasem's American author of Top Ten television program. He is editor of 
the <I>Los Angeles Zagat Restaurant Survey</I>,  <I>Casey's Biggest Hits</I>, 
<I>The Best Restaurants of Los Angeles</I>, and author of <I>Best Restaurants of Los Angeles 
under $10 Guide</I>.<P>

<P>	A film critic for <I>Los Angeles Magazine</I>, Shindler has had articles ranging from 
film and music to food and restaurants appear in <I>Playboy, People, US, Bon Appetite, Traveler, 
Travel & Leisure, The Chicago Tribune, The Los Angeles Times, Diversion Magazine, Alaska 
Airlines Magazine, American Way Magazine, Panorama Magazine, Playgirl,</I> and many more.

<P><P>	Shindler lives in a restored Bauhaus-style home in Cheviot Hills, which has been 
featured in Los Angeles Magazine, and runs five miles a day to keep the weight off.  Shindler 
describes himself as, "Just a big old hungry boy who writes for the fun of it."<P>
<P>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<P>


<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>


