<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>JOE WEST
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>JOE WEST
</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>KMPC MORNING NEWS ANCHOR</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>

<P>        When Southern Californians need their morning news, Joe West is
there for them. He can be heard on 710 TALK / KMPC during the "Peter Tilden
Show with Tracey Miller," which airs from 5:30 to 9 a.m.<P>

<P>        West began his radio career while attending the University of
Northern Colorado. His first radio job, at age 18, was as a disc jockey for
country music stations KYOU-AM and KGRE-FM in Greeley, Colorado. He soon
realized his hunger was for news reporting, and shifted stations to KFKA-AM
and KGBS-FM, which better suited his taste.<P>

<P>        In the early 1980s, Joe began handling a range of duties and
entertainment functions for the NFL's Denver Broncos and the short-lived
USFL's Denver Gold. However, he soon joined the Navy, where he became a
highly decorated serviceman during Operation Desert Storm.<P>

<P>        West was given an honorable discharge after Desert Storm, and moved
to Los Angeles where he was hired by CBS affiliate KNX Newsradio as a news
writer. He later served as the Los Angeles Bureau Chief at Metro Networks
News, and also began doing voice-overs for various radio and television
advertising campaigns. Joe's voice can be heard throughout the Southland
delivering the "on-hold" message for thousands of businesses.<P>

<P>        West enjoys the outdoors and plans to participate in the San
Francisco to Los Angeles AIDS Bike-A-Thon. He also enjoys reading and
working on his old Corvette.<P>
<P>
                    





</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>


