<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ROD'S EARLY-EARLY-EARLY OSCAR PREDICTIONS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR>
<IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="../Bios/white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
<TR>
<TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="../Bios/710talk4.gif"></TD>
<TD>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=4>ROD'S EARLY-EARLY-EARLY OSCAR PREDICTIONS</FONT>
<BR><BR>
Okay, now, I am writing this down in September, so cut me some slack.
</CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="../Bios/white.gif">




<BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=80% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=10>
<TR><TD>
<OL>
<LI>  James Woods will win the Oscar for "The Ghosts of Mississippi."
<BR><BR>
<LI>  No Disney song will be nominated.
<BR><BR>
<LI>  None of the Best Picture nominees will come from before October.
<BR><BR>
<LI>  Castle Rock will have more nominations than any studio ( save for Sony, which distributes CR)
<BR><BR>
<LI>  Mel Gibson will get his first acting nomination for "Ransom"
<BR><BR>
<LI>  Ron Howard AND Rob Reiner will be nominated for best director.
<BR><BR>
<LI>  At least four of the best picture nominees will be films set in the past.
<BR><BR>
<LI>  At least four of the best pic nominees will be over two hours long.
<BR><BR>
<LI>  Daniel day Lewis will be nominated.
<BR><BR>
<LI>  "Hamlet" will be the most nominated film.
<BR><BR>
<LI>Lauren Bacall will at least be nominated and will probably win best
supporting actress for "The Mirror has Two Faces"
<BR><BR>
<LI>"The People Vs. Larry Flynt" will have the award for most noms/no wins this
year.
<BR><BR>
<LI>Courtney Love will be nominated for best supporting actress.
<BR><BR>
<LI>The big winner in Cannes "Secrets and Lies' will NOT be nominated.


</OL>
</TD>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

<BR>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2>I'll offer updates as the come along.</CENTER></FONT>


