<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>LEO TERRELL
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>LEO TERRELL

</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>"TERRELL AND KATZ SHOW"<BR>
Monday - Friday<BR> Noon to 3 p.m.</H3></FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>




<P>	Leo Terrell is a highly respected civil rights attorney and cohost of the "Terrell and Katz Show" airing on 710 TALK / KMPC.
<P>
<P>	Leo and his talk show partner, Burt Katz, bring a "Crossfire" feel to the show with Terrell usually taking the liberal side in contrast to Katz's conservative viewpoints. Their long list of experience in the law field makes them two highly proficient experts in their analysis of current law cases and current events.
<P>
<P>	Terrell is a former High School teacher who graduated from the U.C.L.A Law School. He began his career in civil rights in the State of Arkansas. After passing the California Bar Exam, Terrell returned to Los Angeles, where he established his own law practice. 
<P>
<P>	His law practice in Beverly Hills specializes in employee rights. It includes discrimination of all types, including race gender, age and disability. Leo also focus's on collective bargaining agreements; contract negotiations involving governmental entities; school related issues, such as federal and state legislation involving funding, curriculum and personnel; and personal injury cases. In addition, Terrell conducts seminars on the subject of employee rights and avenues available for the enforcement of such rights.
<P>
<P>	His other credits include acting as Legal Redress Counsel for the Los Angeles Chapter of the NAACP and participation in numerous public service organizations with goals such as the control and elimination of hate-crime and the establishment of improved race relations. In addition, Terrell has provided media commentary on television and radio regarding important civil rights proceedings such as the Rodney King, Reginald Denny and the O.J. Simpson trials.
<P>
</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<P>


<CENTER>###</CENTER>
<P>


