<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>BURT KATZ
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>BURT KATZ
</H1>

		<FONT SIZE=5>"TERRELL AND KATZ SHOW"<BR>Monday - Friday<BR>Noon to 3 p.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>

	<P>Burt Katz, a man whose name is synonymous with the legal profession, is a retired 
Los Angeles Superior Court Judge and cohost of the "Terrell and Katz Show" on 710 TALK / KMPC. <P>

	<P>Katz and his cohost, Leo Terrell, discuss current events and legal issues with the 
hope that they provide a better understanding of the legal system for their radio audience. The 
show promises to be anything but low key, as Katz's conservative views often conflict with 
Terrell's liberal perspective.<P>

	<P>For 25 years, Burt has been involved all aspects of the criminal justice system including 
as a prosecutor, defense attorney, judge, witness, teacher and even as a victim of crime. He also 
 served as a prosecutor in the Los Angeles County District Attorney's office for 14 years. During 
that period, Katz participated in how many famous homicide cases. One of his noted cases was as 
one of the chief prosecutors in the Charles Manson family murders involving the slayings of Gary Hinman 
and Donald "Shorty" Shea.<P> 

	<P>Judge Katz served on the Los Angeles Municipal and Superior Courts for nearly nine years, 
presiding over many controversial and celebrated cases including the strangulation killing of 
actress, Dominque Dunne. Katz has supervised and presided over Juvenile Courts, working closely 
with delinquent children, juvenile judges and child welfare experts.	In additon, Burt has 
served as "Legal Liaison Aide" for the District Attorney of Los Angeles County and was the 
Director of the District Attorney's "Less Lethal Weapons Task Force" in which fifty police 
agencies participated.<P>

	<P>He has taught criminal law and justice, trial advocacy and crime scene investigation at 
law schools, police academies and the California Specialized Training Institute. He has also been 
a consultant to Gavin de Becker, who has developed "Mosaic 5" the pre-incident indicators of 
predictable violence for stalkers. He has also been an instructor at the prestigious California 
Judges Association and C.J.E.R. (Continuing Education for Judges) Institute and lecturer on the 
law throughout the United States.<P>

	<P>Burt has given speeches regarding his legal experience as an attorney, judge and legal 
commentator. He has also been featured as legal expert and commentator on Larry King Live, 
Rivera Live, The Charles Grodin Show, BBC, Canadian Broadcast System, Fox, 
E! Entertainment, Good Morning America, Today Show, America's Talking, Day and Date and various 
Los Angeles TV news programs. During the Simpson Trial, he wrote a weekly column for theMalibu 
Times newspaper titled O.J. Update.<P>

	<P>In addition to being a commentator and broadcaster - Katz is a writer. Over the past 
eight years, he has written about the criminal justice system including a screen play which was 
nominated for the prestigious Diane Thomas Award, a mini-series, and a play which will be 
produced and performed later this year. Currently, Burt is writing a book which is a searing 
analysis of the criminal justice system titled, "May The Judge Approach The People" (What's 
Wrong With The Criminal Justice System). The book will be published early 1997 by Time-Warner 
Books.<P>

</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
