<H2><A HREF="#TK">Recent Events and Updates</A></H2>

<H2><A HREF="#PROGRAMMING">Program Listing</A></H2>

<H2><A HREF="../ScrapBook/home.htm">Scrapbook</A></H2>

</TR>
</TD>
</TABLE>
<BR  CLEAR="ALL">

<IMG WIDTH=90% HEIGHT=3 BORDER=0  SRC="../gifs/redBar.1.gif"><BR><P>

<A NAME="TK"></A>
<TABLE   HEIGHT=30%  WIDTH=80%  BORDER=0  CELLPADDING=0  CELLSPACING=12>

<TR><TH><FONT color=0000FF>710 TALK/KMPC ADDS NEW SHOWS</FONT></TH></TR> 
<TR><TD>
<P>LOS ANGELES - 710 Talk/KMPC announced that Turi Ryder, a female talk show host from Chicago, will replace "Terrell & Katz" 
from noon to 3 p.m. beginning Monday, September 30 and a new weekend schedule will begin, effective October 5, 1996.  The
"Terrell & Katz" program moves to sister-station 790 KABC on weekends from 1 to 4 p.m. in addition, 710 Talk/KMPC will add
weekend restaurant critics Merrill Shindler and Elmer Dills from sister-station 790 KABC.<P>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="#PROGRAMMING">Check Out the New Program Listing Below</A></CENTER>
<BR><BR>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE   HEIGHT=90%  WIDTH=80%  BORDER=0  CELLPADDING=0  CELLSPACING=12>

<TR><TH><FONT color=0000FF>
KMPC RADIO HIRES DAVE COOKE AS NEW 
OPERATIONS MANAGER / PROGRAM DIRECTOR</FONT></TH></TR> 
<TR><TD>


	<P>LOS ANGELES - Maureen Lesourd, KABC / KMPC / KLOS President and General Manager, 
announced today that Dave Cooke has been appointed the new Operations Manager / Program Director 
of KABC and KMPC Radio, effective August 12, 1996.<P>

	<P>Cooke is a News/Talk Radio veteran who has successfully worked as a news director, 
on-air talent, researcher and programming consultant. "Dave brings a tremendous amount of 
knowledge and radio experience to our heritage stations," said Lesourd. "His reputation is 
sterling and he has been heralded by many colleagues as an outstanding programming professional. 
I'm certain that Dave will be a wonderful addition to our team."<P>

	<P>For the past 10 years, he has been a partner in Roberts/Cooke Media Research & Resources 
in San Rafael, California. The company provides programming consulting and research for 
News/Talk radio stations. Some of the firm's clients have included: KRLD-AM Dallas; KMOX-AM St. 
Louis; KIRO-AM/FM Seattle; WCBS-AM New York; KMBZ/KCMO-AM Kansas City; and KXL-AM Portland.<P>

	<P>Prior to founding his company, Cooke was the Vice President & Director of News for RKO 
Radio Networks in New York. In addition, Dave has worked in Boston as the News Director for 
WHDH-AM; served as the News & Public Affairs Director for KHJ-AM in Los Angeles; acted as an 
Anchor and Correspondent for ABC Radio Network in New York; and was News Director of KFRC-AM in 
San Francisco. He began his radio career in the Dallas-Fort Worth market, first as an afternoon 
News Anchor at WFAA-AM and later as the News Director of KNUS-FM.<P>

	<P>"I am very excited about working at KABC / KMPC radio,'" says Cooke. "These are two 
stations with a tremendous heritage, premiere talent and a dynamic general manager. My first 
priority is to help re-focus the stations and ultimately re-claim their dominance." <P>

	<P>Cooke holds a Journalism/Political Science degree from the University of North Texas. 
Andy Ludlum will continue to act as the Program Manager of KABC / KMPC, reporting to Cooke.<P>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>



