<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>TOM LEYKIS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>TOM LEYKIS

</H1>

<FONT SIZE=5>Monday to Friday 3-7 p.m.<BR>
Overnight Replays Weekdays 12-5 a.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>
Tom Leykis, the man who is changing the face of today's talk radio, is host of 710 Talk/KMPC's 
weekday afternoon drive program The Tom Leykis Show from 3 to 7 p.m. Tom's show brings a unique 
dimension to the talk format with a cutting-edge style that draws a new and younger audience.<P>
	
Being the only nationally syndicated talk program to originate from Los Angeles, Tom taps into  
a guest list of Hollywood's elite and outrageous to appear on the show. Guests vary from actors, 
comedians and rock stars to politicians and opinion-makers and there's no telling what particular 
topic he may choose to arouse his audience. In addition to talking with in-studio guests and 
taking calls from listeners across the nation, Tom had no qualms about telling stories about his 
personal life and often provokes his listeners with his opinions.<P>
	
A self-described "computer fanatic," Leykis also intends to bring an interactive element to his show  via the nation's largest commercial computer networks. Subscribers to Prodigy, CompuServe   and American Online will be able to communicate with Leykis 
by posting E-Mail messages to him while his show is on the air.<P>
	
Tom Leykis built his radio career on the air in some of America's largest markets including Los 
Angeles, Boston, Miami and Phoenix. After early stints in markets such as Albany, New York and 
Staunton, Virginia, Leykis moved to Miami where he had the number one rated nighttime talk show. 
In 1985 he became Program Director of Phoenix's KFYI, also serving as the afternoon drive 
personality for three years. In the Spring of 1988, Leykis moved to the L.A. talk radio outlet 
KFI where his afternoon drive show was the highest rated talk program in its time slot. During 
his L.A. term, he gained world-wide attention for many of his wild antics and on-air stunts. 
Then in May of 1993, Leykis moved to Boston where his mid-day show on WRKO Radio helped bring 
the station's Arbitron ranking up from #12 in the summer to #2 in the fall. Tom continued at WRKO until moving back to Los Angeles in the Spring of 1994 to take on his national audience with Westwood One and Los Angeles on 710 Talk/KMPC.<P>


</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<P>


<CENTER>###</CENTER>
<P>


