<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Michael Reagan
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="AA0000" VLINK="BBBB00">
<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>



<TABLE  BORDER=2 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=10  CELLPADDING=8>
	<TR>
     <TD><IMG  WIDTH=167  HEIGHT=115  SRC="710talk4.gif"></TD>

     <TD  ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH=75% >
		<H1>MICHAEL REAGAN</H1>

<FONT SIZE=5>"The Michael Reagan Talk Show"<BR>
Monday to Friday 3 - 7 p.m.</FONT></TD>
	</TR>
<CENTER></TABLE>

<BR><IMG  WIDTH=0  HEIGHT=10  Align=CENTER SRC="white.gif"><BR>

<TABLE  BORDER=0 WIDTH=70% CELLSPACING=0  CELLPADDING=0>

<TD>
	Michael Reagan's talk show, heard on 710 TALK / KMPC in Los Angeles, provides listeners 
a national forum to discuss substantive issues with politicians, opinion leaders and news makers.<P>

	<P>Michael has earned record ratings as the number one host in dozens of markets since he 
started his national radio talk show. His radio career began as a guest host for the Michael 
Jackson Show on KABC Talkradio in Los Angeles. In turn, Reagan was hired as the host of a 
top-rated local radio program in San Diego until he launched his national program in 1992. <P>

	<P>Prior to his radio career, Michael was active in power boat racing, setting six world 
records (he still holds the record for the fastest passage from Ketchikan to Seattle). In total, 
he has raised 1.5 million dollars for the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation, Diabetes Foundation, the 
United States Olympic Committee and the Statute of Liberty Restoration Fund through his racing. 
Michael also received the "Victor Award" for outstanding sports and humanitarian achievement.<P>

	<P>Reagan is the author of a best-selling autobiography, On the Outside Looking In, and the 
forthcoming Making Waves: Bold Exposs On The Issues That Made Michael Reagan Talk Radio's 
Number One Nighttime Host. He is co-author of the Great American Quote Book. Like his father, 
former President of the United States Ronald Reagan, Michael has been an actor.<P> 

	<P>Michael founded the Reagan Information Interchange, which includes his newsletter, the 
Monthly Monitor, and his top-rated World Wide Web site - reagan.com. He has appeared on 
television programs including The Tonight Show, Good Morning America, Today Show and Politically 
Incorrect.<P>

	<P>In addition, Reagan was one of two Americans named an honorary Member of the 104th 
Congress. On the eve of swearing-in of the first Republican Congressional majority in four 
decades and the first "Conservative Opportunity Congress" in history, Michael delivered the 
keynote address to the freshmen Members of Congress.
<P>
	<P>Michael married Colleen Sterns in 1975 and they live with their children, Cameron and 
Ashley, in Sherman Oaks, California. He is also an avid golfer.<P>

</TD>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
<P>
<P>
