<P><IMG src="122_0.gif"></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P><H2>World Congress Against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children</H2></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P><IMG src="122_1.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P><H2>The sex exploiter</H2><BR>

<H4>The people who have sex with children vary from those who choose to engage in this activity, to those who do not care, to those who do not realise.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>First and most easily distinguishable -- but in the minority -- are paedophiles.  Paedophilia is a condition in which adults prefer to have sex with pre-pubescent girls and boys.  Paedophile behaviour follows quite defined patterns:  often paedophiles put themselves in situations where they come regularly into contact with children.  They find relationships with adults difficult but claim to have a &quot;caring&quot; relationship with a child, often suggesting that they are paying the child for sex in order to help the child and its family financially, or to help the child to learn about sex from a caring person.  Paedophiles regularly obtain pornography involving children and are &quot;collectors&quot; of photos, videos and other keepsakes of the children they come into contact with, in order to &quot;freeze&quot; the age of the child and replay it time and again.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>There are also people who do not care whether their sexual partner is a child or not.  The globalised flow of money has increased demand for commercial sex, and many exploiters are local men, often regular users of commercial sex workers, who do not distinguish on the basis of age.  In some cases, demand for children for sex is based on a belief that children are less likely to have had multiple partners, and so are less likely to transmit infection.  In some instances, there are myths that having sex with children can cure disease, rejuvenate or even improve business.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>Some people have sex with children without questioning the age of the partner.  They may be people who, in &quot;normal&quot; circumstances, would not choose to have sex with a child but for a variety of reasons do.  These reasons include:  the freedom of a holiday in a foreign &quot;exotic&quot; location, being drunk or affected by drugs, ignorance or lack of care in recognising the likelihood that an offered partner is under-age.  Such ignorance is not excusable</H4>
<P><CENTER><hr><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="factsheets.htm">Factsheets</A> | <A HREF="theme.htm">Theme Papers</A> | <A HREF="declaration.htm">Declaration</A> | <A HREF="links.htm">Links</A> | <A HREF="press.htm">Press materials</A>  <BR><A HREF="reports.htm">Congress reports</A> | <A HREF="intpress.htm">Interesting press</A> <BR><A HREF="default.htm">CSEC Home Page</A></P></CENTER><hr>
</BODY>
