<BODY>

<P>
<P>
<TABLE border>
<TR valign=top><TD>
<P><IMG src="122_0.gif"></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P><H2>World Congress Against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children</H2></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P><IMG src="122_1.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P><H2>Impact</H2><BR>

<H4>The impact of commercial sexual exploitation on a child is enormous.  The child loses its childhood, its dignity, often its future.  These are unquantifiable costs, but there are consequences of exploitation which are more readily measurable.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The most obvious of these relates to the health of the child. HIV/AIDS is both a cause and a consequence of commercial sexual exploitation of children.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The evidence shows that in some parts of the world, children are being chosen as sex partners in the mistaken belief that sex with a child is safer.  Having sex with a child, it is thought, protects the abuser from HIV/AIDS because the child is more likely to be clean and to have had fewer sex partners.  </H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>Quite the opposite is true.  Because of their vulnerability and weakness, children in prostitution are often forced to take more clients than an adult might accept, and are generally powerless to ask the client to use a condom.    Moreover, children are physically more vulnerable to infection, not only because they are more easily damaged internally (and are often treated with violence by their clients), but also because young membranes are more porous.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The pure virgin child is sought by many customers as the safest bet.  Reconstructive surgery is common practice, so that some commercially sexually exploited children are sold as virgins even though they have had multiple sex partners.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The reality is that many children forced into commercial sex are becoming infected with HIV.  Children rescued from brothels in parts of South East Asia are immediately tested for HIV/AIDS.  Rates of 50 per cent positive are normal, with up to 90 per cent seropositivity being found in some cases.  Not only is this in itself a death sentence, it also means that what is left of a childs life may well be a time of loss of family and community, dignity and options.  HIV-positive children face discrimination and rejection.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>There are other serious physical and psychological repercussions of forcing children into sex.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>Children are robbed of their childhood and of the leisure of formative years.  This deprivation leaves scars that can take years to heal.  Children lose trust in others, particularly adults, and become vulnerable to further exploitation.  They also become more liable to grow into exploiters themselves in turn.  They lose self-respect and dignity, and can develop a range of post-traumatic stress symptoms such as depression, aggression and violence, loss of self-control and self-mutilation.  Their lives frequently end in suicide.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>And there are long-lasting physical effects.  Not only are children trapped in the cycle of commercial sexual exploitation often physically abused, beaten, burned, tortured and deprived of food, air, light and movement, they are also vulnerable to kidney infections, cervical cancer, early and repeated pregnancies, and sexually transmitted diseases.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>Numerous studies have also shown high levels of substance abuse by children involved in prostitution.  Drugs are often used to keep children taken into prostitution submissive.  They may also be a self-medicating means to numb the pain of hunger or despair.  </H4>
<P><CENTER><hr><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="factsheets.htm">Factsheets</A> | <A HREF="theme.htm">Theme Papers</A> | <A HREF="declaration.htm">Declaration</A> | <A HREF="links.htm">Links</A> | <A HREF="press.htm">Press materials</A>  <BR><A HREF="reports.htm">Congress reports</A> | <A HREF="intpress.htm">Interesting press</A> <BR><A HREF="default.htm">CSEC Home Page</A></P></CENTER><hr>
