<P>
<TABLE border>
<TR valign=top><TD>
<P><IMG src="122_0.gif"></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P><H2>World Congress Against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children</H2></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>
<P><IMG src="122_1.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P><H2>The World Congress</H2><BR>

<H4>The World Congress Against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children, which took place in Stockholm, Sweden, from August 27 to 31 1996, was part of the broader process of protecting childrens rights.  It focused on three elements of the commercial sexual exploitation of children:  child prostitution, the trafficking and sale of children for sexual purposes, and child pornography.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The primary purpose of the Congress was to draw international attention to the problems of commercial sexual exploitation of children and to promote the development of national policies and programmes to combat all forms of such exploitation in the specific contexts in which they occur.  To this end, the Congress considerd and adopted a Declaration and Agenda for Action.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The Congress provided an open forum for discussion through workshops and presentation of case studies, in which all segments of society exchanged experiences.  It defined the scope of the problem, explored the underlying causes and the specific forms of commercial sexual exploitation of children in different countries and regions.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>The most important aim, however, was to lay the groundwork for national action by increasing awareness, forging national partnerships and coalitions involving governments, NGOs, civil society and international organisations.  The Congress was only a step in this important process.</H4>
<P>
<P>
<H4>It took place at this time because some aspects of sexual exploitation of children are clearly growing.  The spread of HIV/AIDS and globalisation have led to an increase in exploitation.  Additionally, the international community has become increasingly aware of the problem, and the level of outrage has grown.  This Congress was the first international attempt to co-ordinate international co-operation on transnational issues and to bring together international players.</H4>
<P><CENTER><hr><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="factsheets.htm">Factsheets</A> | <A HREF="theme.htm">Theme Papers</A> | <A HREF="declaration.htm">Declaration</A> | <A HREF="links.htm">Links</A> | <A HREF="press.htm">Press materials</A>  <BR><A HREF="reports.htm">Congress reports</A> | <A HREF="intpress.htm">Interesting press</A> <BR><A HREF="default.htm">CSEC Home Page</A></P></CENTER><hr>
