<TR valign=top><TD>
<P>      <BR>
<CENTER><BIG><B>World Congress Against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children</B></BIG></CENTER><BR>
1,879 people, including 718 government representatives from 122 countries, 105 delegates of UN and other inter-governmental organisations, 471 non-governmental organisation representatives, 47 youth/co-sponsor delegates and 538 members of the world's press, met in Stockholm, Sweden, 27 - 31 August 1996 at the first World Congress against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children.<BR>
<BR>
In the words of the General Rapporteur, Professor Vitit Muntarbhorn of Thailand, &quot;there can be no more delusions&quot; -- no-one can deny that the problem of children being sold for sex exists, here and now, in almost every country in the world.<BR>

<P>A Declaration and Agenda for Action (see &quot;Declaration&quot;) were unanimously adopted and strategic alliances formed to fight against those who sell and buy children for sex.  Updates of documents at this site are in progress.<BR>

<P><CENTER> <p><form method = "POST" action="/scripts/inotes.exe/Search/Local/csechome.NSF?1e2"><input name = "SEARCH" size = 30>  <input type="submit" name = "SREQUEST" value = "Search"><input type="submit" name = "SREQUEST" value = "Options"></form>
</CENTER></TD><TD>
